- Build docker image
  To simly build a docker image: Docker build .
  To build and tag: Docker build -t docker-image-name .
  If want to build an image and push to  your hub, use your usename + "/" before the docker image name: Docker build -t hungpv1988/docker-image-name
  https://docs.docker.com/guides/docker-concepts/building-images/writing-a-dockerfile/
  
   
- Run a docker: docker run -d -p 8080:8080 docker-image-name 
  "-p" is to map docker port and host. We could ignore host port if needed.
  "-d" is to say that docker run as a background process -> need to verify.
 https://docs.docker.com/guides/docker-concepts/running-containers/publishing-ports/   

- Read guidelines here https://docs.google.com/document/d/1UXuGc4Obn9gEowUHV-t4K6ENXG4Zl4wIYHJB1m_alK4/edit